snippet.textDisplay: My cat doesn't shed that much for me to try this project if I wanted to . . . and if I did do it, somehow, I know she would hate it because she hated her kittens that she had before I could afford to get her spayed. I had to raise her children while she took very important catnaps away from them and then I got all four of them fixed and sent them off into the world with their adoptive families. A couple with two children took two kittens so at least two of them are together somewhere, out there. My cat acted like she didn't even remember she had kittens and went about her life as usual, no grief whatsoever, never looked for them. So yeah, i think if I did this project, Phoebe would just destroy it because it resembles a kitten. She hates children. Thankfully she is fixed and won't be having any more of them. Sometimes parents just aren't meant to be parents.
